bundances, both gas-phase and grain-surface reactions are needed.\n  Conclusions. CH$_3$CCH is a molecule whose brightness and abundance in many\ndifferent regions can be utilised to provide a benchmark of molecular variation\nwith the physical properties of star-forming regions. It is essential when\nmaking such comparisons, that the abundances are determined with a good\nunderstanding of the spatial scale of the emitting region, to ensure that\naccurate abundances are derived.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 29 Sep 2019 17:50:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-13"}
