{"id":"1910.00009","submitter":"Sergey A. Trigger","authors":"S.A. Trigger, S. A. Maslov","title":"Primordial plasma: influence of non-ideality on equilibrium radiation","comments":"7 pages, 2 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.plasm-ph cond-mat.stat-mech","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The asymptotic behavior of the equilibrium radiation in Maxwellian plasma is\nstudied for the low--frequency region. It is shown, that the equilibrium\nradiation can essentially deviate from the Planck law even for a weakly\nnon-ideal plasma. The deviation from the Planck distribution is described by\nthe transverse dielectric permittivity which takes into account both frequency\nand spatial dispersion. The influence of plasma non-ideality increases with the\nnon-ideality parameter in the dielectric permittivity. The spectral energy\ndistribution of the equilibrium radiation essentially changes in the region of\nobservable frequencies. At asymptotically low frequencies, the equilibrium\nradiation begins to exhibit power behavior instead the logarithmic one. The\nresults indicate that the spectral energy distribution of radiation could be\ndifferent then the Planck one in the primordial plasma of the early Universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Sep 2019 10:42:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 19 Apr 2020 10:15:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-21"}
